[normal]&#xa0;[bold]2.1.
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]Between 1976 and 2012 there have been a total of 68 reportable accidents, of which 11 involved fatalities, in the 
[normal]UK
[normal]’s offshore oil and gas support operations. The Chart below, which does not take 
[normal]account of the accidents in 2013, presents the annual accident rates. Clearly, from the early 1990s the accident rate improved markedly but has levelled off since.
